SUMMARY:Earth Month at Evergreen Brick Works
DESCRIPTION:Earth Month at Evergreen Brick Works is a month-long celebration of practical ways to live more sustainably. 🌍 \nEach Sunday and select Saturdays in April\, join us for a full schedule of public programming that brings Toronto’s sustainability community together in one of the city’s most unique spaces. \nFrom hands-on workshops and expert presentations to community walks\, eco-arts installations\, and curated marketplaces\, Earth Month at the Brick Works is where environmental curiosity meets real-world action for all ages. \nLearn more & register for workshops: https://www.evergreen.ca/evergreen-brick-work/events/earth-month-2026/
URL:https://nowtoronto.com/event/earth-month-at-evergreen-brick-works/
LOCATION:Evergreen Brick Works\, Evergreen Brick Works\, 550 Bayview Ave\, Toronto\, ON M4W 3X8\, Canada\, Old Toronto\, Toronto\, Ontario\, M4W 3X8
CATEGORIES:Community Events,Festivals,Kids & Family
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/png:https://nowtoronto.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/earth-month-at-evergreen-brick-works.png
END:VEVENT
