SUMMARY:Sing-Along! Jesus Christ Superstar
DESCRIPTION:Easter weekend means one thing–it’s time for the annual Jesus Christ Super Star sing-along! \nDirected by the late great Norman Jewison\, this adaptation by Andrew Lloyd Webber and Tim Rice transposes the Passion Play into a dazzling rock opera. The final days of Jesus’ (Ted Neely) life play out through the perspective of Judas Iscariot\, charged with electric music and powerful imagery meant to be experienced on the big screen. \nBefore the film begins\, join music director Douglas Price for a harmony lesson for one of the film’s most iconic songs. Then get ready to celebrate Easter Sunday singing and dancing the whole film through.
URL:https://nowtoronto.com/event/sing-along-jesus-christ-superstar/
LOCATION:2236 Queen Street East\, 2236 Queen St E\, Toronto\, ON M4E 1G2\, Canada\, Old Toronto\, Toronto\, Ontario\, M4E 1G2
CATEGORIES:Film & Media
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/png:https://nowtoronto.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/sing-along-jesus-christ-superstar.png
END:VEVENT
