SUMMARY:Two Strangers Trying Not to Kill Each Other
DESCRIPTION:4 stars “excellent…a powerful insight into a life shared by two charismatic creatives” – The Guardian \nWhen artist Maggie Barrett (75) breaks her femur\, her husband Joel Meyerowitz (84)\, a world-famous photographer\, becomes her caregiver. In the shadow of mortality\, each with a long and dramatic life behind them\, the hard truths of life together provoke in Maggie and Joel an attempt to find a shared inner-peace while there is still time.
URL:https://nowtoronto.com/event/two-strangers-trying-not-to-kill-each-other/
LOCATION:Hot Docs Ted Rogers Cinema\, 506 Bloor Street West\, Toronto\, M5S 1Y3
CATEGORIES:Film & Media
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/png:https://nowtoronto.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/two-strangers-trying-not-to-kill-each-other.png
END:VEVENT
