SUMMARY:Ceza
DESCRIPTION:TURKISH HIP-HOP TITAN CEZA TO HEADLINE TORONTO’S LULA LOUNGE ON APRIL 5TH \nEvent Schedule: \nDoors: 7:00 PM \nDJ set: 8:00 PM \nArtist set: 8:30 PM \n \nThe MTV Award-Winner and Global Speed-Rap Pioneer Brings His 25-Year Legacy to Toronto. \nOn April 5\, 2026\, the heart of downtown Toronto will pulse with the rhythm of Istanbul as Turkish rap legend Cezatakes the stage at Lula Lounge. \nKnown for his breathtaking “double-time” flow and lyrical depth\, Ceza’s arrival in Toronto marks a significant cultural moment\, bringing one of the most technical performers in hip-hop history to Canada’s premier new intimate venue. \nWith a career spanning over two decades\, Ceza has consistently broken barriers for international hip-hop: \n\nHistoric Firsts: He was the first-ever Turkish artist to win an MTV Europe Music Award (Best Turkish Act) and the first to be featured on NPR’s prestigious “Best Songs of the Year” list with his hit “Suspus”.\nGlobal Collaborations: Ceza solidified his international status with his legendary verse on Tech N9ne’s “Worldwide Choppers\,” collaborating with global icons like Busta Rhymes and Twista.\nStreaming Powerhouse: With hundreds of millions of streams on Spotify and YouTube\, his anthems like “Yerli Plaka” and “Neyim Var Ki” remain the gold standard of the genre\, resonating with millions across the globe.\n\n“Music is the only bridge that doesn’t require a passport\,” says Ceza. “Toronto has always been a dream destination for this tour. I can’t wait to bring the energy of my latest work and the classics to the Lula stage.” \nAbout Ceza: Ceza is the most influential figure in Turkish rap history. From his underground beginnings in Istanbul to his global accolades\, he has defined the genre through his speed\, poetic lyricism\, and relentless stage presence.
URL:https://nowtoronto.com/event/ceza/
LOCATION:Lula Lounge\, 1585 Dundas St W\, Toronto\, M6K 1T9
CATEGORIES:Live Music
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/png:https://nowtoronto.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/ceza.png
END:VEVENT
